frameDefinitions: The Focal_feature is defined in relation to a Landmark_feature, either as a particular part, or as an immediately bordering entity.
This frame contains nouns denoting a rank or level within an established hierarchy.
This frame contains words that describe specific aspects of a Color.
In this frame, there is a Part of a Whole in which the Part is defined with respect to the canonical or inherent orientation of the Whole.
This frame is about Items in the state of occupying a certain Rank within a hierarchy.
An Entity changes from a Prior_state to a Post_state in a sequence that follows a pre-defined plan, expectation, or model of change.
frameExamples: I'm on the <t>summit</t> of Mt. Shasta.
He <t>ranks</t> second in his class in mathematics.
